i)\n*''[[Cavalleria rusticana]]'' and ''[[Pagliacci]]'' ([[Marcelo \u00c1lvarez]], [[Eva-Maria Westbroek]], [[Patricia Racette]],  conducted by [[Fabio Luisi]])\n{{Div col end}}\n\n===2015\u20132016===\n{{Div col|colwidth=30em|rules=yes}}\n*''[[Il trovatore]]'' ([[Anna Netrebko]], [[Yonghoon Lee]], [[Dmitri Hvorostovsky]], [[Dolora Zajick]],  conducted by {{ill|Marco Armiliato|it}})\n*''[[Otello]]'' ([[Aleksandr Antonenko]], [[Sonya Yoncheva]], [[\u017deljko Lu\u010di\u0107]],  conducted by [[Yannick N\u00e9zet-S\u00e9guin]])\n*''[[Tannh\u00e4user (opera)|Tannh\u00e4user]]'' ([[Johan Botha (tenor)|Johan Botha]], [[Eva-Maria Westbroek]], [[Peter Mattei]], [[Michelle DeYoung]],  conducted by [[James Levine]])\n*''[[Lulu (opera)|Lulu]]'' ([[Marlis Petersen]], [[Susan Graham]], [[Johan Reuter]],  conducted by [[Lothar Koenigs]])\n*''[[Les p\u00eacheurs de perles]]'' ([[Matthew Polenzani]], [[Diana Damrau]], [[Mariusz Kwiecie\u0144]],  conducted by [[Gianandrea Noseda]])\n*''[[Turandot]]'' ([[Nina Stemme]], Marco Berti, [[Anita Hartig]],  conducted by [[Paolo Carignani]])\n*''[[Manon Lescaut]]''  ([[Krist\u012bne Opolais]], [[Roberto Alagna]], Massimo Cavalletti,  conducted by [[Fabio Luisi]])\n*''[[Madama Butterfly]]'' ([[Krist\u012bne Opolais]], [[Roberto Alagna]], [[Dwayne Croft]],  conducted by [[Karel Mark Chichon]])\n*''[[Roberto Devereux]]'' ([[Sondra Radvanovsky]], [[Matthew Polenzani]], [[El\u012bna Garan\u010da]], [[Mariusz Kwiecie\u0144]],  conducted by [[Maurizio Benini]])\n*''[[Elektra (opera)|Elektra]]'' <ref>[http://www.metopera.org/metopera/liveinhd/live-in-hd-2015-16-season \"2015\u201316 Live in HD Schedule\"], on metopera.org</ref> ([[Nina Stemme]], [[Waltraud Meier]], [[Adrianne Pieczonka]], [[Eric Owens (bass-baritone)|Eric Owens]],  conducted by [[Esa-Pekka Salonen]])\n{{Div col end}}\n\n===2016\u20132017===\nThe 2016-2017 season included the presentation of the first opera by a female composer in the series, ''[[L'Amour de loin]]'' of Kaija Saariaho, which also marked the first opera in the series to feature a female conductor, [[Susanna M\u00e4lkki]]. The presentation of ''[[Der Rosenkavalier]]'' marked the final performances in their respective roles by [[Ren\u00e9e Fleming]] (the Marschallin) and [[El\u012bna Garan\u010da]] (Octavian).<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/13/arts/music/renee-fleming-final-bow-der-rosenkavalier.html | title=Watch Ren\u00e9e Fleming Take Her Final Bow in ''Der Rosenkavalier''|work=[[The New York Times]]| author=Michael Cooper | date=2017-05-13 | accessdate=2017-05-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.wqxr.org/story/stopping-clocks-strauss-der-rosenkavalier | title=Stopping the Clocks With Strauss' ''Der Rosenkavalier''|publisher=[[WQXR-FM|WQXR]]|author=Merrin Lazyan|date=2017-05-11|accessdate=2017-05-17}}</ref>\n{{Div col|colwidth=30em|rules=yes}}\n*''[[Tristan und Isolde]]'' ([[Nina Stemme]], [[Stuart Skelton]], Ekaterina Gubanova, [[Ren\u00e9 Pape]], conducted by Sir Simon Rattle)\n*''[[Don Giovanni]]'' ([[Simon Keenlyside]], [[Hibla Gerzmava]], [[Malin Bystr\u00f6m]], [[Paul Appleby (tenor)|Paul Appleby]], [[Adam Plachetka]] conducted by [[Fabio Luisi]])\n*''[[L'Amour de loin]]'' ([[Eric Owens (bass-baritone)|Eric Owens]], [[Susanna Phillips]], Tamara Mumford, conducted by [[Susanna M\u00e4lkki]])\n*''[[Nabucco]]'' ([[Pl\u00e1cido Domingo]], [[Liudmyla Monastyrska]], Dimitry Belosselskiy, [[Jamie Barton]], conducted by [[James Levine]])\n*''[[Rom\u00e9o et Juliette]]'' ([[Diana Damrau]], [[Vittorio Grigolo]], [[Mikhail Petrenko (bass)|Mikhail Petrenko]], Elliot Madore, Virginie Verrez, conducted by Gianndrea Noseda)\n*''[[Rusalka (opera)|Rusalka]]'' ([[Krist\u012bne Opolais]], [[Brandon Jovanovich]], [[Jamie Barton]], [[Eric Owens (bass-baritone)|Eric Owens]], [[Katarina Dalayman]], conducted by [[Mark Elder]])\n*''[[La traviata]]'' ([[Sonya Yoncheva]], [[Michael Fabiano]], [[Thomas Hampson]], conducted by [[Nicola Luisotti]])\n*''[[Idomeneo]]'' ([